<a name="newsitem956083094,94908,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">ROK Shipping Woes</font> </strong><small>Posted Tuesday, April 18, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
If you are like most other Everquest players you have probably already ordered your copy of Ruins of Kunark. It has become painfully apparent however that most of these players have not yet received a copy of the game or even so much as a confirmation. Some players have already been billed yet have not received either/or. I am one of those players. After a day full of phone calls and emails I have decided to post up my feelings on the matter along with a collection of information for everyone else who is confused out there. It can be found by clicking <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/rokwoes.html">here</a>.<br><br>New Editorial: <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/rokwoes.html">ROK Woes</a>.
</p>
<a name="newsitem956079362,56868,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">John Smedley Interview</font> </strong><small>Posted Tuesday, April 18, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
<a href="http://www.gamespot.co.uk">Gamespot UK</a> has posted up an <a href="http://www.gamespot.co.uk/news/2000/04/6565.html">Interview with John Smedley</a> of Verant. Quotage below...<br><br><blockquote>GameSpot UK: What would you say to the idea that EverQuest is fading, turning into a fashion show?<br><br>Smedley: We have over 200,000 players now. The average EverQuest player does something like 20 hours per week. That's not fading. Some are playing five to six hours per day every week. Is that healthy? Well... They're going to be doing it anyway, browsing the web and so on. It may as well be something enjoyable like this.</blockquote>
</p>
<a name="newsitem956029828,610,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Patch Day</font> </strong><small>Posted Monday, April 17, 2000 by <a href="mailto:nofx@gameznet.com">NoFx</a></small><br>
More Kunark stuff.<br><br><blockquote>April 17th, 4:00pm<br>-------------------<br><br>EverQuest: The Ruins of Kunark (upgrade) should now be arriving on doorsteps around the world.  Please note that attempting to create an Iksar character will not work until the expansion zones are officially opened within the next week.  <br><br>We ask that if you attempt to create an Iksar character out of curiosity that you do not proceed past the "History" page (the page that speaks of your lifestyle) in the character creation process.  Once at this page, please use the "Back" button to get back to the character creation screen.  Pressing "Next" on this screen will cause the name you have selected to go into the "used name" list, making it unavailable for future use.  <br><br>We appreciate your cooperation.<br><br>- The EverQuest Team<br><br>*Today's Patch*<br><br>Today's patch consisted of preparations for the launch of Kunark, as well as some new art.  The following spell changes were also included:<br><br>- Corrected a bug with a new bard song that allowed them to charm anything, such as deities and dragons.<br>- Added a lesser included wisdom effect with "Brilliance" as well as a lesser included intelligence effect with "Insight".  These spells will no longer stack.<br><br><br>- The EverQuest Team</blockquote>
</p>
<a name="newsitem955993121,49517,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">A Journey Into Everquest</font> </strong><small>Posted Monday, April 17, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
Nick Yee dropped me a mail to inform me that he has opened his <a href="http://www.students.haverford.edu/nyee/everquest/start.html">Journey Into Everquest</a> to the public. A couple months back he held a survey of Everquest players. From the data he collected this page was born.
</p>
<a name="newsitem955934097,68541,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Faction Database Update</font> </strong><small>Posted Sunday, April 16, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
I just posted an updated version of the <a href="http://gamezportal.com/eqr/faction.shtml">Faction Database</a>. This version includes a couple of new factions and fills in some blanks on some of the older factions as well.<br><br>Updated Database: <a href="http://gamezportal.com/eqr/faction.shtml">Faction Database</a>.
</p>
<a name="newsitem955696714,74581,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Faction Database Update</font> </strong><small>Posted Friday, April 14, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
I just posted up a decent sized update to our faction database. You can find the faction database at <a href="http://www.gamezportal.com/eqr">EQ Reference</a> or directly by clicking <a href="http://gamezportal.com/eqr/faction.shtml">here</a>. If you find any faction adjustments that are not listed feel free to let us know about them by clicking <a href="mailto:eqstaff@gameznet.com">here</a>.<br><br>Updated Feature: <a href="http://gamezportal.com/eqr/faction.shtml">Faction Database</a>.
</p>
<a name="newsitem955580299,23409,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Ruins of Kunark Giveaway</font> </strong><small>Posted Wednesday, April 12, 2000 by <a href="mailto:nofx@gameznet.com">NoFx</a></small><br>
Looks like another page is giving away Ruins of Kunark:<br><br><blockquote>Neriak.COM is happy to announce we are giving away two copies of the Ruins of Kunark expansion in a writing contest!  For more details, see the news item at<a href="http://www.neriak.com/">http://www.neriak.com/</a><br><br>Good luck! :)</blockquote>
</p>
<a name="newsitem955580220,45656,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">EQ Gathering 3</font> </strong><small>Posted Wednesday, April 12, 2000 by <a href="mailto:nofx@gameznet.com">NoFx</a></small><br>
Sound like another night of fun:<br><br><blockquote>Hello!<br> <br>I am one of the organizers of the EverQuest Gathering 2 that was held in Saint Louis last month. We are in the process of putting together our third event and would appreciate any help you could give us by posting the announcement on your board.<br> <br>Due to some problems with the server on our home site, we have had to use a temporary site for our announcement. We would appreciate the following post, as we are ready to now start taking registrations and getting things prepared for the next big event! <br> <br>EverQuest Gathering 3 will be held on July 9th in Las Vegas!! Once again, there will be activities and games with prizes! This is a great chance to get to know your fellow players! And we have also been promised another delegation of representatives from Verant will be present to meet you and answer your questions! <br> <br>To register to attend or to find out more information, visit <a href="http://eqgathering.bizland.com/">http://eqgathering.bizland.com/</a><br> <br>Thanks so much!<br>Cindy</blockquote>
</p>
